nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoAlgorithm.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoAlgorithm
nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoAlgorithm.description: The algorithm used to determine the timeout value used for retransmitting unacknowledged octets.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoMin.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoMin
nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoMin.description: The minimum value permitted by a TCP implementation for the retransmission timeout, measured in milliseconds. More refined semantics for objects of this type depend upon the algorithm used to determine the retransmission timeout. In particular, when the timeout algorithm is rsre(3), an object of this type has the semantics of the LBOUND quantity described in RFC 793.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoMax.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoMax
nscDxTcpXcelTcpRtoMax.description: The maximum value permitted by a TCP implementation for the retransmission timeout, measured in milliseconds. More refined semantics for objects of this type depend upon the algorithm used to determine the retransmission timeout. In particular, when the timeout algorithm is rsre(3), an object of this type has the semantics of the UBOUND quantity described in RFC 793.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpMaxConn.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpMaxConn
nscDxTcpXcelTcpMaxConn.description: The limit on the total number of TCP connections the entity can support. In entities where the maximum number of connections is dynamic, this object should contain the value -1.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpActiveOpens.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpActiveOpens
nscDxTcpXcelTcpActiveOpens.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the SYN-SENT state from the CLOSED state.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpPassiveOpens.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpPassiveOpens
nscDxTcpXcelTcpPassiveOpens.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the SYN-RCVD state from the LISTEN state.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpAttemptFails.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpAttemptFails
nscDxTcpXcelTcpAttemptFails.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the SYN-SENT state or the SYN-RCVD state, plus the number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the LISTEN state from the SYN-RCVD state.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpEstabResets.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpEstabResets
nscDxTcpXcelTcpEstabResets.description: The number of times TCP connections have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the ESTABLISHED state or the CLOSE-WAIT state.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpCurrEstab.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpCurrEstab
nscDxTcpXcelTcpCurrEstab.description: The number of TCP connections for which the current state is either ESTABLISHED or CLOSE- WAIT.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpInSegs.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpInSegs
nscDxTcpXcelTcpInSegs.description: The total number of segments received, including those received in error. This count includes segments received on currently established connections.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpOutSegs.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpOutSegs
nscDxTcpXcelTcpOutSegs.description: The total number of segments sent, including those on current connections but excluding those containing only retransmitted octets.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpRetransSegs.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpRetransSegs
nscDxTcpXcelTcpRetransSegs.description: The total number of segments retransmitted - that is, the number of TCP segments transmitted containing one or more previously transmitted octets.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnTable.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnTable
nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnTable.description: A table containing TCP connection-specific information.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnEntry.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnEntry
nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnEntry.description: Information about a particular current TCP connection. An object of this type is transient, in that it ceases to exist when (or soon after) the connection makes the transition to the CLOSED state.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpSapId.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpSapId
nscDxTcpXcelTcpSapId.description: The SAP ID number for this TCP listener.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpHostIdx.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpHostIdx
nscDxTcpXcelTcpHostIdx.description: The logical host number for this TCP connection.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpHostName.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpHostName
nscDxTcpXcelTcpHostName.description: The logical host name for this TCP connection.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnState.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnState
nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnState.description: The state of this TCP connection.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnLocalAddress.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnLocalAddress
nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnLocalAddress.description: The local IP address for this TCP connection. In the case of a connection in the listen state which is willing to accept connections for any IP interface associated with the node, the value 0.0.0.0 is used.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnLocalPort.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnLocalPort
nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnLocalPort.description: The local port number for this TCP connection.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnRemAddress.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnRemAddress
nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnRemAddress.description: The remote IP address for this TCP connection.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnRemPort.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnRemPort
nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnRemPort.description: The remote port number for this TCP connection.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpInErrs.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpInErrs
nscDxTcpXcelTcpInErrs.description: The total number of segments received in error (e.g., bad TCP checksums).

nscDxTcpXcelTcpOutRsts.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpOutRsts
nscDxTcpXcelTcpOutRsts.description: The number of TCP segments sent containing the RST flag. This object is not supported in this version.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnAttempt.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnAttempt
nscDxTcpXcelTcpConnAttempt.description: The total number of connections initiated.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpClosed.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpClosed
nscDxTcpXcelTcpClosed.description: The total number of connections closed.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpSegsTimed.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpSegsTimed
nscDxTcpXcelTcpSegsTimed.description: The total number of segments we tried to get rtt.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpRttUpdated.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpRttUpdated
nscDxTcpXcelTcpRttUpdated.description: The total number of rtt segments updated.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpDelAck.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpDelAck
nscDxTcpXcelTcpDelAck.description: The total number of delayed acks sent.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpTimeoutDrop.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpTimeoutDrop
nscDxTcpXcelTcpTimeoutDrop.description: The total number of conn. dropped in rxmt timeout.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpRexmtTimeo.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpRexmtTimeo
nscDxTcpXcelTcpRexmtTimeo.description: The total number of retransmit timeouts.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpPersistTimeo.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpPersistTimeo
nscDxTcpXcelTcpPersistTimeo.description: The total number of persist timeouts.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepTimeo.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepTimeo
nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepTimeo.description: The total number of keepalive timeouts.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepProbe.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepProbe
nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepProbe.description: The total number of keepalive probes sent.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepDrop.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepDrop
nscDxTcpXcelTcpKeepDrop.description: The total number of connections dropped in keepalive.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpSndPack.name: nscDxTcpXcelTcpSndPack
nscDxTcpXcelTcpSndPack.description: The total number of data packets sent.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpSndByte.description: The total number of data bytes sent.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpSndRexmitPack.description: The total number of data packets retransmitted.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpSndRexmitByte.description: The total number of data bytes retransmitted.

nscDxTcpXcelTcpSndAcks.description: The total number of ack-only packets sent.
